  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study used an external endocardial acceleration sensor (sonR sensor), placed on the
      patient's chest, to time the closure of aortic and mitral valves, and compared its
      performance with echocardiography.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
